                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On both sides of the entrance into the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Maṅgaḷapurīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Palaeographically this record may be assigned to the 16th century A.D. It is in verse and praises the <hi rend="bold">Toṇḍaikāvalaṉ.</hi> The Pāṇḍya and the Chōḷa are stated to have been begging for their country and crown respectively.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
